.TH NCALC 1 "March 2026" "ncalc 3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ncalc \- Terminal Scientific Calculator & CAS with Advanced Calculus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ncalc
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ncalc
is a terminal-based Computer Algebra System (CAS). It uses the \fBGiNaC\fR library for symbolic computation and \fBncursesw\fR for a UTF-8 enabled split-window interface.

.SH COMMAND SYNTAX
.SS Solving Equations
Use the \fBfind\fR command (Ctrl+f) to solve for a specific variable.
.IP "find x, 2x = 10"
Solves linear equations. Result: \fBx = 5\fR.
.IP "find y, y^2 = 4x"
Solves quadratic equations. Result: \fBy = {2*sqrt(x), -2*sqrt(x)}\fR.

.SS Derivatives
.IP "diff(sin(x), x)"
Standard symbolic derivative.
.IP "df/dx(1,0) where f(x,y) = x^2 + y^2"
Calculates the partial derivative with respect to x at the point (1,0). The \fBwhere\fR clause is triggered by \fBCtrl+w\fR.

.SS Integrals
Use the syntax \fBi(upper,lower), expr dvar\fR.
.IP "i(2,0), x^2 dx"
Definite integral of x^2 from 0 to 2. Calculated numerically via Simpson's Rule. Result: \fBA = 2.666667\fR.

.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.SS General
.IP "Ctrl + g"
Toggle between Calculator and Graph modes.
.IP "Ctrl + f"
Insert "find " command.
.IP "Ctrl + w"
Insert " where " clause.
.IP "Tab"
Switch focus between the Input and History panels.
.IP "q"
Quit the application.

.SS Math Shortcuts
.IP "Ctrl + d"
Insert \fBdiff(\fR.
.IP "Alt + f"
Insert \fBf(\fR.
.IP "Alt + u, l, e, v"
Insert placeholders \fBupper\fR, \fBlower\fR, \fBexpr\fR, and \fBdvar\fR for integration.
.IP "s, c, t"
Insert \fBsin(\fR, \fBcos(\fR, \fBtan(\fR.
.IP "i"
Insert integral command \fBi(\fR.
.IP "Ctrl + p, e, n"
Insert constants \fBPi\fR, \fBexp(1)\fR (Euler's number), and \fBI\fR (Imaginary unit).

.SS Graph Mode
.IP "j / k"
Zoom Out / In.
.IP "+ / -"
Zoom In / Out.
.IP "Arrows"
Zoom (depending on terminal support).

